## Task Solution:

**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

**Tower Structure:**
- **Count & Layers:** The tower structure is composed of 11 blocks and has 7 layers.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
    - Layer 1 (Base): Two red curved blocks (block type resembling index 1 in dictionary) are placed side-by-side horizontally.
    - Layer 2: Two yellow rectangular blocks (block type resembling index 6 in dictionary) are placed side-by-side horizontally on top of Layer 1, oriented perpendicular to Layer 1.
    - Layer 3: Two red curved blocks (block type resembling index 1 in dictionary) are placed side-by-side horizontally on top of Layer 2, oriented parallel to Layer 1.
    - Layer 4: One yellow rectangular block (block type resembling index 8 in dictionary) is placed horizontally centered on top of Layer 3.
    - Layer 5: Two green rectangular blocks (block type resembling index 5 in dictionary) are placed vertically side-by-side on top of Layer 4.
    - Layer 6: One yellow rectangular block (block type resembling index 6 in dictionary) is placed horizontally on top of Layer 5, spanning across both green blocks.
    - Layer 7 (Top): One red triangular block (block type resembling index 16 in dictionary) is placed centered on top of Layer 6.

**Small Structure:**
- **Count & Layers:** The small structure is composed of 3 blocks and has 3 layers.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
    - Layer 1 (Base): One green rectangular block (block type resembling index 4 in dictionary) is placed horizontally.
    - Layer 2: One orange cylindrical block (block type resembling index 9 in dictionary) is placed vertically centered on top of Layer 1.
    - Layer 3 (Top): One orange triangular block (block type resembling index 13 in dictionary) is placed on top of Layer 2.
